Privileged Identity Management (PIM) is a service to manage/control/access important resources in your organization
resources like Microsoft entra id , microsoft 365 , intune

only authorized users have access to sensitive data and system



sing Privileged Identity Management requires licenses

Privileged Identity Management provides time-based and approval-based role activation

Key features
just in time access
Require approval to activate privileged roles
enforce mfa
Use justification to understand why users activate
Get notifications when privileged roles are activated
conduct access reviews to ensure users still need roles
ownload audit history for internal or external audit


Who can do what?
roles in Privileged Identity Management ,
only a user who is in the Privileged Role Administrator or Global Administrator role can manage assignments for other administrators
only a subscription administrator, a resource Owner, or a resource User Access administrator can manage assignments for other administrators


Users who are Privileged Role Administrators, Security Administrators,
or Security Readers don't by default have access to view assignments to Azure resource roles in Privileged Identity Management.

Roles
permanent eligible	Duration	A role assignment where a user is always eligible to activate the role.
permanent active	Duration	A role assignment where a user can always use the role without performing any actions.
time-bound eligible	Duration	A role assignment where a user is eligible to activate the role only within start and end dates.
time-bound active               A role assignment where a user can use the role only within start and end dates.